Lewis %26 Clark took a battle of two-win squads. Meanwhile Davenport won easily in a non-league matchup. Darnay Tripp , KREM.com 11:12 p.m. PDT October 8, 2015 Central Valley's shutout of North Central keeps them in the running for first place in the GSL 4A race. Central Valley's shutout of North Central keeps them in the running for first place in the GSL 4A race. (Photo: KREM 2) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Central Valley stayed perfect in Greater Spokane League 4A action Thursday night. 
The Bears led 23-0 over North Central at the half, and rolled to a 43-0 victory. CV is now 2-0 in league games. 
In the nightcap at Albi Stadium Lewis & Clark took a battle of two-win teams. The Tigers beat Rogers 21-3. 
Thursday's games weren't limited to the GSL. Davenport hosted DeSales in a non-league showdown. The Gorillas raced to a 52-21 win thanks in part to three touchdown runs by Loran Boggs. Read or Share this story: http://on.krem.com/1Rxaal4 TOP VIDEOS
